 bake for a further 5 minutes (180°C) until lightly golden. Remove from oven and leave to cool. Turn oven temperature down to 160°C. Meanwhile, make filling."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Filling"},{"content":"Place dark chocolate in mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 9<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then melt <b>4 min\/50°C\/speed 1<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside. Clean mixing bowl."},{"content":" <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place eggs, egg yolks and caster sugar in mixing bowl then whisk <b>10 min\/37°C\/speed 3<b>."},{"content":"Add melted dark chocolate and mix <b>20 sec\/speed 1<b>. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong> and finish mixing by hand with spatula if necessary."},{"content":"Spread caramel over base of tart case then pour over chocolate mixture. Clean mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place white chocolate in mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 9<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then melt <b>3 min\/50°C\/speed 1<b>. Transfer to a piping bag fitted with a thin nozzle (2-3 mm), pipe lines of white chocolate across dark chocolate then drag a cocktail stick across the lines to create a pattern. Bake for 15-20 minutes (160°C) until set (may have a slight wobble)."},{"content":"Leave to cool then serve warm or at room temperature."}],"hintsAndTricks":["This decadent tart is a dinner party version of the popular teatime treat - millionaire’s shortbread. Simple to make, yet so impressive to serve to your friends and family, enjoy warm drizzled with double cream for the ultimate indulgence.","Can also be made in a rectangular tart tin <b>(36 cm x 12 cm)<b> or fluted round tart tin <b>(Ø 22 cm).<b>"],"basicInfo":["medium","35m","2h 20m","9 portions"]}